<section xml:id="s_continuity">
  <title>Continuity</title>

  <definition xml:id="d_continuity_at_a_point">
    <title>Continuity at a point</title>
    <idx><h>continuity</h><h>at a point</h></idx>
    <statement>
      <p>
      Let <m>f</m>  be a real-valued function with domain <m>D\subseteq \mathbb{R}</m>. Given <m>c\in D</m>, we say <term><m>f</m> is continuous at <m>c</m></term> if one of the conditions below is met.
      <ul>
        <li>
          <title> Interior point</title>
          <p>
          The input <m>c</m> is an interior point of <m>D</m>, the limit of <m>f</m> as <m>x</m> approaches <m>c</m> exists, and
          <me>
          \lim\limits_{x \to c} f(x)=f(c)
          </me>.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <title> Left endpoint</title>
          <p>
            The input <m>c</m> is a <term>left endpoint</term> of the domain (<ie />, <m>c</m> is not an interior point, and <m>D</m> contains an interval of the form <m>[c, d)</m>), the limit of <m>f</m> as <m>x</m> approaches <m>c</m> from the right exists, and
            <me>
              \lim\limits_{x \to c^+} f(x)=f(c)
            </me>.
          </p>
        </li>
          <li>
            <title> Right endpoint</title>
            <p>
              The input <m>c</m> is a <term>right endpoint</term> of the domain (<ie />, <m>c</m> is not an interior point, and <m>D</m> contains an interval of the form <m>(b,c]</m>), the limit of <m>f</m> as <m>x</m> approaches <m>c</m> from the left exists, and
              <me>
                \lim\limits_{x \to c^-} f(x)=f(c)
              </me>.
            </p>
        </li>
      </ul>
      </p>
    </statement>
  </definition>
  <definition xml:id="d_continuous">
    <statement>
      <p>
        Let <m>f</m> be a real-valued function with domain <m>D\subseteq \mathbb{R}</m>. We say <m>f</m> is <term>continuous</term> if it is continuous at all inputs <m>c\in D</m>. 
      </p>
    </statement>
  </definition>
